<item>
            <title>[FELIX-4451] HttpContext#getResource is called with a relative path</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-4451</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a resource is registered through the HttpService with an HttpContext, the getResource() method is called with a relative path, stripping off the leading slash, e.g.&lt;br/&gt;
httpService.registerResources(&quot;/foo&quot;, &quot;/foo&quot;, myContext)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If /foo/a is requested myContext.getResource(&quot;foo/a&quot;) is called.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The leading slash should not be removed&lt;/p&gt;</description>
